BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:feminist-gaming-fellowship-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T142451Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260712
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260713
SUMMARY:Deadline: Feminist Gaming Fellowship: Open Call 2026
DESCRIPTION:The Feminist Gaming Project is opening applications for its fir
 st Fellowship cohort: five fellows from different creative and research fi
 elds spending three months developing 3D assets\, tools\, and documentatio
 n for its Open Access Asset Library (OAL)\, a free\, open repository of in
 clusive 3D content created by\, with\, and for intersectionally feminist a
 nd diverse communities. Where mainstream marketplaces default to hyper-ath
 letic\, idealized\, or hyper-sexualized characters\, the OAL offers averag
 e bodies\, real postures\, everyday objects\, and the kinds of lives most 
 games leave out (pregnancy and postpartum\, care work\, ageing\, disabilit
 y\, domestic labor). This first cohort is dedicated to 3D content. Support
 ed by the Creative Industries Fund NL and working across the Netherlands\,
  Türkiye\, Germany\, and the UK\, the project challenges exclusionary nor
 ms in how games are made. The fellowship offers a EUR 1\,000 honorarium pe
 r fellow over three months (half at start\, half on completion)\; mentorsh
 ip from the core team and advisors in feminist design\, game studies\, 3D 
 production\, and digital culture\; a peer community across NL\, TR\, DE\, 
 and the UK with biweekly meetings\; visibility through a travelling exhibi
 tion program\, publications\, and public events\; and authorship credited 
 in the OAL under its license terms. Five roles are recruited (one fellow e
 ach): 3D Character Artist for inclusive base meshes\; 3D Character Artist 
 for pregnancy and postpartum assets\; 3D Animator for neutral and everyday
  movement\; 3D Modeller for domestic and care-labor environments\; and Res
 earcher/Writer for documentation and the representation framework\; applic
 ants may rank up to two. Open to 3D artists\, animators\, modellers\, desi
 gners\, researchers\, and writers committed to inclusive and intersectiona
 l representation in games\; prior game-industry experience is not required
 \, and emerging creators\, underrepresented practitioners\, and researcher
 s at the intersection of games\, gender\, and culture are especially encou
 raged\, particularly those based in or connected to NL\, TR\, DE\, or the 
 UK. To apply\, email feministgamingproject@gmail.com with a short statemen
 t (max ~500 words)\, a portfolio or work samples (a link is fine)\, and co
 nfirmation of availability for the three-month period\; name the role(s) i
 n the subject line or statement. The project explicitly asks applicants to
  write statements in their own voice rather than using AI-generated text. 
 Indicative timeline: applications close 12 July 2026\; selection and notif
 ication late July\; fellowship period August to October 2026\; showcase an
 d publication November to December 2026.\n\nOrganisation: Feminist Gaming 
 Project\nLocation: Remote across the Netherlands\, Türkiye\, Germany\, an
 d the UK\nAward: EUR 1\,000 honorarium per fellow (paid half at the start\
 , half on completion)\nDuration: Three months\, August to October 2026\; m
 inimum ~6 hours per week (~75 hours total)\n\nMore: https://feministgaming
 .com/fellowship/index.html?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_mediu
 m=referral
URL:https://feministgaming.com/fellowship/index.html?utm_source=artificialn
 ouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote across the Netherlands\, Türkiye\, Germany\, and the UK
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:play-creative-gaming-festival-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T142451Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260628
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260629
SUMMARY:Deadline: PLAY26 Creative Gaming Festival: Open Call for Games & Pl
 ayful Media Works
DESCRIPTION:PLAY is all about the creative use of digital games\, combining
  this culture with media art\, discourse and education. This year's theme\
 , 'Hey\, listen! (Music & Emotion)'\, relates to mixtape culture and the s
 haring of bonds and feelings with the people you like and love. The open c
 all invites artists and developers to submit games or playful media works 
 (including alt.ctrl\, interactive theatre and performances) for one of thr
 ee strands: the Creative Gaming Awards (works that let players get creativ
 e in or with them\, including the Most Creative Game Award)\; the core exh
 ibition 'Hey\, listen!' (works fitting this year's Music & Emotion theme)\
 ; and Focus Hamburg (a Local Artists Feature for artists and developers ba
 sed in Hamburg). All games shown in the festival exhibition are eligible f
 or the Audience Award\, chosen by festival visitors and honoured at the Aw
 ards Show. Selected projects are showcased to an international audience. N
 OTE: this is a festival exhibition and awards open call rather than a paid
  grant\; no artist fee is stated. The Call for Games & Playful Media Works
  is open until 28 June 2026 (Calls for Talks and Workshops follow). Submit
  via https://www.playfestival.de/en/play26-submissions-are-open.\n\nOrgani
 sation: PLAY - Creative Gaming Festival\nLocation: Hamburg\, Germany\; int
 ernational submissions welcome (with a Focus Hamburg feature for artists a
 nd developers based in Hamburg).\nAward: Exhibition and awards opportunity
 \, NOT a paid grant: selected works are showcased to an international fest
 ival audience. Awards include the Most Creative Game Award and an Audience
  Award (all games in the festival exhibition are eligible\, voted on by fe
 stival visitors). No artist fee is stated.\nDuration: Festival 2026 (exhib
 ition and awards show)\n\nMore: https://www.playfestival.de/en/play26-subm
 issions-are-open?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.playfestival.de/en/play26-submissions-are-open?utm_source=a
 rtificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Hamburg\, Germany\; international submissions welcome (with a Focu
 s Hamburg feature for artists and developers based in Hamburg).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:she-got-game-emerging-talents-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T142451Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Game Design Emerging Talents: She Got Game
DESCRIPTION:She Got Game is a Pro Helvetia mentoring programme promoting eq
 ual opportunities in the Swiss and international game industry\, supportin
 g the representation of women in management positions through dialogue wit
 h experienced international experts from the game industry. The call is ai
 med at professional game designers who identify as women from the regions 
 of Pro Helvetia's liaison offices: the Arab region\, East Asia\, South Ame
 rica\, South Asia and Vietnam\, and West\, Central\, East and Southern Afr
 ica. ELIGIBILITY: Emerging Talents are game developers or game studios who
 se relevant training or registration (self-employed\, sole proprietorship\
 , or company) dates back less than seven years. Selection criteria include
  digital content for devices such as computers\, consoles\, mobile devices
 \, or mixed-reality devices requiring a high level of interaction\; clearl
 y defined objectives in terms of participation and career\; originality\, 
 feasibility\, degree of innovation\, and marketability of the project\; an
 d project leaders holding the copyright and rights of use. Excluded: commi
 ssioned work and projects that are part of an advertising or promotional c
 ampaign\, and purely technological projects without obvious narrative and/
 or aesthetic content. WHAT IS OFFERED: individual coaching and input talks
  on project development\, business strategy and finances\, marketing\, PR\
 , and pitch training\; involvement in a growing community of female game d
 evelopers\; potential access to international trade fairs\; CHF 3\,000 tow
 ard the production of a prototype or demo version\; and up to CHF 250 per 
 week toward childcare or children's travel expenses when attending interna
 tional trade fairs (a budget must be presented in advance). All modules ar
 e conducted in English\; the programme is a time-consuming commitment of r
 oughly 30 hours over six months\, plus potential additional time attending
  events or trade fairs. APPLICATION: submit a short CV (including educatio
 n/training\, nationality\, and residency status in Switzerland)\, a short 
 description of the current project (type and genre\, gameplay\, platform\,
  development status\, target audience\, with relevant visual material\, ma
 x. 10 A4 pages)\, a project portfolio\, and expectations regarding the pro
 gramme's objectives. All documents should be submitted in English\; if not
  possible\, applications may be submitted in German\, French\, or Italian.
  KEY DATES: applications open 1 July 2026\; submission deadline 1 Septembe
 r 2026\, 23:59 CEST\; notification of decision in November 2026\; earliest
  project start 1 January 2027. Apply via the Pro Helvetia application port
 al.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Remote/i
 nternational mentoring programme\; applicants must be based in one of Pro 
 Helvetia's liaison-office regions (Arab region\, East Asia\, South America
 \, South Asia and Vietnam\, and West\, Central\, East and Southern Africa)
 .\nAward: CHF 3\,000 toward the production of a prototype or demo version\
 , plus individual coaching and community access\; potential access to inte
 rnational trade fairs. When attending trade fairs\, applicants with childc
 are responsibilities can request up to CHF 250 per week for childcare or c
 hildren's travel expenses. No application fee.\nDuration: Six-month mentor
 ing programme\, approximately 30 hours total commitment\; notification in 
 November 2026\; earliest project start 1 January 2027.\n\nMore: https://pr
 ohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/game-design-emerging-talents-she-got-game-3/?
 utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/game-design-emerging-talents-she
 -got-game-3/?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Remote/international mentoring programme\; applicants must be base
 d in one of Pro Helvetia's liaison-office regions (Arab region\, East Asia
 \, South America\, South Asia and Vietnam\, and West\, Central\, East and 
 Southern Africa).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prohelvetia-game-design-pre-production-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T142451Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Game Design Emerging Talents: Pre-Production
DESCRIPTION:Pro Helvetia's Game Design Emerging Talents pre-production gran
 t supports early-career game designers in developing playable prototypes f
 or digital games. Emerging Talents are game developers or studios whose ga
 me-design education or company foundation dates back less than seven years
 . ELIGIBILITY: requires a connection to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, o
 r permanent residency with regular artistic activity in Switzerland)\; not
  open to practitioners without a Swiss connection. At least 50 percent of 
 participants must be Swiss citizens or permanent residents whose place of 
 work is in Switzerland. AMOUNT: up to CHF 20\,000\, plus possible addition
 al coaching. Deadlines twice a year: 1 March (23:59 CET) and 1 September (
 23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia portal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helve
 tia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Switzerland-based emerging game design
 ers and studios.\nAward: Up to CHF 20\,000\, plus possible additional coac
 hing. No application fee.\nDuration: Pre-production / prototype phase\; de
 adlines twice yearly (1 March and 1 September).\n\nMore: https://prohelvet
 ia.ch/en/find-support/game-design-emerging-talents-pre-production?utm_sour
 ce=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/game-design-emerging-talents-pre
 -production?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Switzerland-based emerging game designers and studios.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prohelvetia-game-design-production-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260712T142451Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Game Design Emerging Talents: Production
DESCRIPTION:Pro Helvetia's Game Design Emerging Talents production grant fu
 nds the production of digital games based on advanced prototypes or vertic
 al slices. Emerging Talents are studios whose game-design education or com
 pany foundation dates back less than seven years. Applicants must be legal
  entities (sole proprietorships accepted if willing to convert). ELIGIBILI
 TY: requires a connection to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, or permanent
  residency with regular artistic activity in Switzerland)\; not open to pr
 actitioners without a Swiss connection. At least 50 percent of participant
 s must be Swiss citizens or permanent residents whose place of work is in 
 Switzerland. AMOUNT: up to CHF 50\,000\, requiring a matching grant of equ
 al value from own or third-party funding. Deadlines twice a year: 1 March 
 (23:59 CET) and 1 September (23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia porta
 l.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Switzerla
 nd-based emerging game studios.\nAward: Up to CHF 50\,000\, requiring a ma
 tching grant of equal value from own or third-party funding. No applicatio
 n fee.\nDuration: Production phase\; deadlines twice yearly (1 March and 1
  September).\n\nMore: https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/game-design-e
 merging-talents-production?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_mediu
 m=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/game-design-emerging-talents-pro
 duction?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Switzerland-based emerging game studios.
END:VEVENT
